Heightened Awareness. Gain a +2 bonus to initiative rolls.
Evasive Maneuvering. Opportunity attacks against the Security Officer are made with disadvantage.
Actions
Bladed Assault. Melee Attack: +8 to hit, dealing 19 (3d8 + 6) slashing damage with a combat knife. If the target is below half hit points, they must succeed on a DC 12 Constitution saving throw or become incapacitated until the end of their next turn. If the target is incapacitated, the Security Officer can use Lethal Precision as a bonus action.
Lethal Precision. Melee Attack: +8 to hit, dealing 22 (3d10 + 6) piercing damage with a tactical sidearm. This action can only be used on a creature that is incapacitated as a result of Bladed Assault.
Containment Tactics. The Security Officer unleashes a series of precise strikes aimed at subduing a target. The target must make a DC 12 Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the target takes 30 (4d12 + 4) bludgeoning damage and is grappled until the end of the Security Officer's next turn. The Security Officer can only use this action once per short rest.